<div id="v230.70.1"><span class="H5329 s">To the chief Musician</span><span class="H1732 s">, <i>A Psalm</i> of David</span><span class="H2142 s">, to bring to remembrance</span><span class="H430 s">. <i>Make haste</i>, O God</span><span class="H5337 s">, to deliver</span><span class="H2363 s"> me; make haste</span><span class="H5833 s"> to help</span><span class="H3068 s"> me, O LORD</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (to helpâ€¦: Heb. to my help)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.70.2"><span class="H954 s">Let them be ashamed</span><span class="H2659 s"> and confounded</span><span class="H1245 s"> that seek</span><span class="H5315 s"> after my soul</span><span class="H5472 s">: let them be turned</span><span class="H268 s"> backward</span><span class="H3637 s">, and put to confusion</span><span class="H2655 s">, that desire</span><span class="H7451 s"> my hurt</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.70.3"><span class="H7725 s">Let them be turned back</span><span class="H6118 s"> for a reward</span><span class="H1322 s"> of their shame</span><span class="H559 s"> that say</span><span class="H1889 s">, Aha</span><span class="H1889 s">, aha</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.70.4"><span class="H1245 s">Let all those that seek</span><span class="H7797 s"> thee rejoice</span><span class="H8055 s"> and be glad</span><span class="H157 s"> in thee: and let such as love</span><span class="H3444 s"> thy salvation</span><span class="H559 s"> say</span><span class="H8548 s"> continually</span><span class="H430 s">, Let God</span><span class="H1431 s"> be magnified</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.70.5"><span class="H6041 s">But I <i>am</i> poor</span><span class="H34 s"> and needy</span><span class="H2363 s">: make haste</span><span class="H430 s"> unto me, O God</span><span class="H5828 s">: thou <i>art</i> my help</span><span class="H6403 s"> and my deliverer</span><span class="H3068 s">; O LORD</span><span class="H309 s">, make no tarrying</span>.</div></div> 
